Meeting 1.3 – System Design Planning
Date: 04 March 2026
Time: 10:00 – 10:45
Attendees: All Members
Agenda:
Design system structure and components
Discussion:
The overall architecture of the system was planned using object-oriented principles.
The structure of the Car class was defined, including attributes such as ID, brand, price, 
location, and availability. The Node class was designed to support the Binary Search Tree structure, 
containing references to left and right child nodes. The BST logic for insertion, searching, and 
deletion was also outlined. Additionally, the menu system flow was discussed to ensure smooth user interaction.
Outcome:
System architecture designed
Core classes and relationships defined
